[{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"#Usage-and-performance-notes-1","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"LightQuery is most performant when the number of columns is short compared to the number of rows. Otherwise, compile-time might swamp run-time, and I'd suggest using DataFrames instead. In addition, due to the limits of inference, LightQuery will not be performant if there are more than 30 columns.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"You can avoid most allocations in LightQuery by keeping your data pre-sorted. If your data is not pre-sorted, then the majority of run-time will likely be spent in sorting.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"LightQuery requires that all of your columns have the same indices. The Rows constructor will check whether this is the case; to override these checks, use @inbounds.","category":"page"},{"location":"#Tutorial-1","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Tutorial","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"I'm using the data from the dplyr tutorial. The data is in the test folder of this package.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"I created it with the following R code:","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"library(nycflights13)\nsetwd(\"C:/Users/hp/.julia/dev/LightQuery/test\")\nwrite.csv(airports, \"airports.csv\", na = \"\", row.names = FALSE)\nwrite.csv(flights, \"flights.csv\", na = \"\", row.names = FALSE)\nwrite.csv(weathers, \"weather.csv\", na = \"\", row.names = FALSE)","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"Import tools from Dates, TimeZones, and Unitful and change the working directory.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"julia> using LightQuery\n\njulia> using Dates: Date, DateTime, Hour\n\njulia> using TimeZones: Class, Local, TimeZone, VariableTimeZone, ZonedDateTime\n\n\n\njulia> using Unitful: °, °F, ft, hr, inch, mbar, mi, minute\n\n\njulia> cd(joinpath(pathof(LightQuery) |> dirname |> dirname, \"test\"));","category":"page"},{"location":"#Airports-cleaning-1","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Airports cleaning","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"Use CSV.File to import the airports data.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"julia> import CSV\n\njulia> airports_file = CSV.File(\"airports.csv\", missingstrings = [\"\", \"\\\\N\"]);","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"For this package, I made named_tuples to replace NamedTuples. Use @name to work with them.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"Get row_info.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"julia> const Airport = row_info(airports_file);","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"Read the first row.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"julia> airport = Airport(first(airports_file))\n((name\"faa\", \"04G\"), (name\"name\", \"Lansdowne Airport\"), (name\"lat\", 41.1304722), (name\"lon\", -80.6195833), (name\"alt\", 1044), (name\"tz\", -5), (name\"dst\", \"A\"), (name\"tzone\", \"America/New_York\"))","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"rename.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"julia> airport = @name rename(airport,\n            airport_code = name\"faa\",\n            altitude = name\"alt\",\n            daylight_savings = name\"dst\",\n            latitude = name\"lat\",\n            longitude = name\"lon\",\n            time_zone = name\"tzone\",\n            time_zone_offset = name\"tz\"\n        )\n((name\"name\", \"Lansdowne Airport\"), (name\"airport_code\", \"04G\"), (name\"altitude\", 1044), (name\"daylight_savings\", \"A\"), (name\"latitude\", 41.1304722), (name\"longitude\", -80.6195833), (name\"time_zone\", \"America/New_York\"), (name\"time_zone_offset\", -5))","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"remove redundant data.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"julia> airport = @name remove(airport,\n            name\"daylight_savings\",\n            name\"time_zone_offset\"\n        )\n((name\"name\", \"Lansdowne Airport\"), (name\"airport_code\", \"04G\"), (name\"altitude\", 1044), (name\"latitude\", 41.1304722), (name\"longitude\", -80.6195833), (name\"time_zone\", \"America/New_York\"))","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"Add units with transform.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"julia> airport = @name transform(airport,\n            altitude = airport.altitude * ft,\n            latitude = airport.latitude * °,\n            longitude = airport.longitude * °\n        )\n((name\"name\", \"Lansdowne Airport\"), (name\"airport_code\", \"04G\"), (name\"time_zone\", \"America/New_York\"), (name\"altitude\", 1044 ft), (name\"latitude\", 41.1304722°), (name\"longitude\", -80.6195833°))","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"Get a true TimeZone. Use @if_known to handle missing data. Note the data contains some LEGACY timezones. Use a type annotation: TimeZone is unstable without it.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"julia> get_time_zone(time_zone) = TimeZone(\n            (@if_known time_zone),\n            Class(:STANDARD) | Class(:LEGACY)\n        )::VariableTimeZone;\n\njulia> @name get_time_zone(airport.time_zone)\nAmerica/New_York (UTC-5/UTC-4)","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"Use the chaining macro @> to chain calls together.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"julia> function get_airport(row)\n            @name @> Airport(row) |>\n            rename(_,\n                airport_code = name\"faa\",\n                altitude = name\"alt\",\n                daylight_savings = name\"dst\",\n                latitude = name\"lat\",\n                longitude = name\"lon\",\n                time_zone = name\"tzone\",\n                time_zone_offset = name\"tz\"\n            ) |>\n            remove(_,\n                name\"daylight_savings\",\n                name\"time_zone_offset\",\n            ) |>\n            transform(_,\n                altitude = _.altitude * ft,\n                latitude = _.latitude * °,\n                longitude = _.longitude * °,\n                time_zone = get_time_zone(_.time_zone)\n            )\n        end;\n\n\njulia> get_airport(first(airports_file))\n((name\"name\", \"Lansdowne Airport\"), (name\"airport_code\", \"04G\"), (name\"altitude\", 1044 ft), (name\"latitude\", 41.1304722°), (name\"longitude\", -80.6195833°), (name\"time_zone\", tz\"America/New_York\"))","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"over each row.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"julia> airports = over(airports_file, get_airport);\n\n\njulia> first(airports)\n((name\"name\", \"Lansdowne Airport\"), (name\"airport_code\", \"04G\"), (name\"altitude\", 1044 ft), (name\"latitude\", 41.1304722°), (name\"longitude\", -80.6195833°), (name\"time_zone\", tz\"America/New_York\"))","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"Call make_columns then Rows to store the data column-wise but view it row-wise. Peek to view.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"julia> airports = Rows(make_columns(airports));\n\n\njulia> Peek(airports)\nShowing 4 of 1458 rows\n|                    name\"name\" | name\"airport_code\" | name\"altitude\" | name\"latitude\" | name\"longitude\" |                name\"time_zone\" |\n| -----------------------------:| ------------------:| --------------:| --------------:| ---------------:| ------------------------------:|\n|             Lansdowne Airport |                04G |        1044 ft |    41.1304722° |    -80.6195833° | America/New_York (UTC-5/UTC-4) |\n| Moton Field Municipal Airport |                06A |         264 ft |    32.4605722° |    -85.6800278° |  America/Chicago (UTC-6/UTC-5) |\n|           Schaumburg Regional |                06C |         801 ft |    41.9893408° |    -88.1012428° |  America/Chicago (UTC-6/UTC-5) |\n|               Randall Airport |                06N |         523 ft |     41.431912° |    -74.3915611° | America/New_York (UTC-5/UTC-4) |","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"index airports by code.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"julia> const indexed_airports = @name index(airports, name\"airport_code\");\n\n\njulia> indexed_airports[\"JFK\"]\n((name\"name\", \"John F Kennedy Intl\"), (name\"airport_code\", \"JFK\"), (name\"altitude\", 13 ft), (name\"latitude\", 40.639751°), (name\"longitude\", -73.778925°), (name\"time_zone\", tz\"America/New_York\"))","category":"page"},{"location":"#Flights-cleaning-1","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Flights cleaning","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"Use CSV.File to import the flights data.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"julia> flights_file = CSV.File(\"flights.csv\");","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"Get the first flight, rename, remove, and transform to add units.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"julia> const Flight = row_info(flights_file);\n\njulia> flight =\n        @name @> flights_file |>\n        first |>\n        Flight |>\n        rename(_,\n            arrival_delay = name\"arr_delay\",\n            arrival_time = name\"arr_time\",\n            departure_delay = name\"dep_delay\",\n            departure_time = name\"dep_time\",\n            destination = name\"dest\",\n            scheduled_arrival_time = name\"sched_arr_time\",\n            scheduled_departure_time = name\"sched_dep_time\",\n            tail_number = name\"tailnum\"\n        ) |>\n        remove(_,\n            name\"arrival_time\",\n            name\"departure_time\",\n            name\"hour\",\n            name\"minute\",\n            name\"time_hour\"\n        ) |>\n        transform(_,\n            air_time = _.air_time * minute,\n            arrival_delay = _.arrival_delay * minute,\n            departure_delay = _.departure_delay * minute,\n            distance = _.distance * mi\n        )\n((name\"year\", 2013), (name\"month\", 1), (name\"day\", 1), (name\"carrier\", \"UA\"), (name\"flight\", 1545), (name\"origin\", \"EWR\"), (name\"destination\", \"IAH\"), (name\"scheduled_arrival_time\", 819), (name\"scheduled_departure_time\", 515), (name\"tail_number\", \"N14228\"), (name\"air_time\", 227 minute), (name\"arrival_delay\", 11 minute), (name\"departure_delay\", 2 minute), (name\"distance\", 1400 mi))","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"Find the time_zone of the airport the flight departed from. Use @if_known to handle missing data.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"julia> airport = @if_known @name get(indexed_airports, flight.origin, missing)\n((name\"name\", \"Newark Liberty Intl\"), (name\"airport_code\", \"EWR\"), (name\"altitude\", 18 ft), (name\"latitude\", 40.6925°), (name\"longitude\", -74.168667°), (name\"time_zone\", tz\"America/New_York\"))\n\njulia> time_zone = @if_known @name airport.time_zone\nAmerica/New_York (UTC-5/UTC-4)","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"Use divrem(_, 100) to split the scheduled_departure_time.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"julia> @name divrem(flight.scheduled_departure_time, 100)\n(5, 15)","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"Create a ZonedDateTime.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"julia> @name ZonedDateTime(\n            flight.year,\n            flight.month,\n            flight.day,\n            divrem(flight.scheduled_departure_time, 100)...,\n            time_zone\n        )\n2013-01-01T05:15:00-05:00","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"All together:","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"julia> get_time(indexed_airports, flight, airport, time) =\n            @name ZonedDateTime(\n                flight.year,\n                flight.month,\n                flight.day,\n                divrem(time, 100)...,\n                @if_known (\n                    @if_known get(indexed_airports, airport, missing)\n                ).time_zone\n            );\n\njulia> @name get_time(\n            indexed_airports,\n            flight,\n            flight.origin,\n            flight.scheduled_departure_time\n        )\n2013-01-01T05:15:00-05:00","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"We can do the same for the scheduled_arrival_time.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"julia> arrival = @name get_time(\n            indexed_airports,\n            flight,\n            flight.destination,\n            flight.scheduled_arrival_time\n        )\n2013-01-01T08:19:00-06:00","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"All together.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"julia> function get_flight(indexed_airports, row)\n            @name @> row |>\n            Flight |>\n            rename(_,\n                arrival_delay = name\"arr_delay\",\n                arrival_time = name\"arr_time\",\n                departure_delay = name\"dep_delay\",\n                departure_time = name\"dep_time\",\n                destination = name\"dest\",\n                scheduled_arrival_time = name\"sched_arr_time\",\n                scheduled_departure_time = name\"sched_dep_time\",\n                tail_number = name\"tailnum\"\n            ) |>\n            remove(_,\n                name\"arrival_time\",\n                name\"departure_time\",\n                name\"hour\",\n                name\"minute\",\n                name\"time_hour\"\n            ) |>\n            transform(_,\n                air_time = _.air_time * minute,\n                distance = _.distance * mi,\n                departure_delay = _.departure_delay * minute,\n                arrival_delay = _.arrival_delay * minute,\n                scheduled_departure_time =\n                    get_time(indexed_airports, _, _.origin, _.scheduled_departure_time),\n                scheduled_arrival_time =\n                    get_time(indexed_airports, _, _.destination, _.scheduled_arrival_time)\n            ) |>\n            remove(_,\n                name\"year\",\n                name\"month\",\n                name\"day\"\n            )\n        end;\n\n\njulia> get_flight(indexed_airports, first(flights_file))\n((name\"carrier\", \"UA\"), (name\"flight\", 1545), (name\"origin\", \"EWR\"), (name\"destination\", \"IAH\"), (name\"tail_number\", \"N14228\"), (name\"air_time\", 227 minute), (name\"distance\", 1400 mi), (name\"departure_delay\", 2 minute), (name\"arrival_delay\", 11 minute), (name\"scheduled_departure_time\", ZonedDateTime(2013, 1, 1, 5, 15, tz\"America/New_York\")), (name\"scheduled_arrival_time\", ZonedDateTime(2013, 1, 1, 8, 19, tz\"America/Chicago\")))","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"over each row. Use @_ to create an anonymous function.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"julia> flights =\n        @> flights_file |>\n        over(_, @_ get_flight(indexed_airports, _));\n\njulia> flights =\n        flights |>\n        make_columns |>\n        Rows;\n\n\njulia> Peek(flights)\nShowing 4 of 336776 rows\n| name\"carrier\" | name\"flight\" | name\"origin\" | name\"destination\" | name\"tail_number\" | name\"air_time\" | name\"distance\" | name\"departure_delay\" | name\"arrival_delay\" | name\"scheduled_departure_time\" | name\"scheduled_arrival_time\" |\n| -------------:| ------------:| ------------:| -----------------:| -----------------:| --------------:| --------------:| ---------------------:| -------------------:| ------------------------------:| ----------------------------:|\n|            UA |         1545 |          EWR |               IAH |            N14228 |     227 minute |        1400 mi |              2 minute |           11 minute |      2013-01-01T05:15:00-05:00 |    2013-01-01T08:19:00-06:00 |\n|            UA |         1714 |          LGA |               IAH |            N24211 |     227 minute |        1416 mi |              4 minute |           20 minute |      2013-01-01T05:29:00-05:00 |    2013-01-01T08:30:00-06:00 |\n|            AA |         1141 |          JFK |               MIA |            N619AA |     160 minute |        1089 mi |              2 minute |           33 minute |      2013-01-01T05:40:00-05:00 |    2013-01-01T08:50:00-05:00 |\n|            B6 |          725 |          JFK |               BQN |            N804JB |     183 minute |        1576 mi |             -1 minute |          -18 minute |      2013-01-01T05:45:00-05:00 |                      missing |","category":"page"},{"location":"#Flights-validation-1","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Flights validation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"Theoretically, the distances between two airports is always the same. Make sure this is the case in our data. First, order by origin, destination, and distance. Then Group By the same variables.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"julia> paths_grouped =\n        @name @> flights |>\n        order(_, (name\"origin\", name\"destination\", name\"distance\")) |>\n        Group(By(_, (name\"origin\", name\"destination\", name\"distance\")));\n","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"Each Group contains a key and value","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"julia> path = first(paths_grouped);\n\n\njulia> key(path)\n((name\"origin\", \"EWR\"), (name\"destination\", \"ALB\"), (name\"distance\", 143 mi))\n\njulia> value(path) |> Peek\nShowing 4 of 439 rows\n| name\"carrier\" | name\"flight\" | name\"origin\" | name\"destination\" | name\"tail_number\" | name\"air_time\" | name\"distance\" | name\"departure_delay\" | name\"arrival_delay\" | name\"scheduled_departure_time\" | name\"scheduled_arrival_time\" |\n| -------------:| ------------:| ------------:| -----------------:| -----------------:| --------------:| --------------:| ---------------------:| -------------------:| ------------------------------:| ----------------------------:|\n|            EV |         4112 |          EWR |               ALB |            N13538 |      33 minute |         143 mi |             -2 minute |          -10 minute |      2013-01-01T13:17:00-05:00 |    2013-01-01T14:23:00-05:00 |\n|            EV |         3260 |          EWR |               ALB |            N19554 |      36 minute |         143 mi |             34 minute |           40 minute |      2013-01-01T16:21:00-05:00 |    2013-01-01T17:24:00-05:00 |\n|            EV |         4170 |          EWR |               ALB |            N12540 |      31 minute |         143 mi |             52 minute |           44 minute |      2013-01-01T20:04:00-05:00 |    2013-01-01T21:12:00-05:00 |\n|            EV |         4316 |          EWR |               ALB |            N14153 |      33 minute |         143 mi |              5 minute |          -14 minute |      2013-01-02T13:27:00-05:00 |    2013-01-02T14:33:00-05:00 |","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"All we need is the key.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"julia> paths =\n        @> paths_grouped |>\n        over(_, key) |>\n        make_columns |>\n        Rows;\n\n\njulia> Peek(paths)\nShowing 4 of 226 rows\n| name\"origin\" | name\"destination\" | name\"distance\" |\n| ------------:| -----------------:| --------------:|\n|          EWR |               ALB |         143 mi |\n|          EWR |               ANC |        3370 mi |\n|          EWR |               ATL |         746 mi |\n|          EWR |               AUS |        1504 mi |","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"Find the number of distinct distances.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"julia> distinct_distances =\n        @name @> paths |>\n        Group(By(_, (name\"origin\", name\"destination\"))) |>\n        over(_, @_ transform(key(_),\n            number = length(value(_))\n        ));\n\n\njulia> Peek(distinct_distances)\nShowing at most 4 rows\n| name\"origin\" | name\"destination\" | name\"number\" |\n| ------------:| -----------------:| ------------:|\n|          EWR |               ALB |            1 |\n|          EWR |               ANC |            1 |\n|          EWR |               ATL |            1 |\n|          EWR |               AUS |            1 |","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"See when there are multiple distances for the same path:","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"julia> @name @> distinct_distances |>\n        when(_, @_ _.number != 1) |>\n        Peek\nShowing at most 4 rows\n| name\"origin\" | name\"destination\" | name\"number\" |\n| ------------:| -----------------:| ------------:|\n|          EWR |               EGE |            2 |\n|          JFK |               EGE |            2 |","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"Peek at flights going to \"EGE\" using when.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"julia> @name @> flights |>\n        when(_, @_ _.destination == \"EGE\") |>\n        Peek\nShowing at most 4 rows\n| name\"carrier\" | name\"flight\" | name\"origin\" | name\"destination\" | name\"tail_number\" | name\"air_time\" | name\"distance\" | name\"departure_delay\" | name\"arrival_delay\" | name\"scheduled_departure_time\" | name\"scheduled_arrival_time\" |\n| -------------:| ------------:| ------------:| -----------------:| -----------------:| --------------:| --------------:| ---------------------:| -------------------:| ------------------------------:| ----------------------------:|\n|            UA |         1597 |          EWR |               EGE |            N27733 |     287 minute |        1726 mi |             -2 minute |           13 minute |      2013-01-01T09:28:00-05:00 |    2013-01-01T12:20:00-07:00 |\n|            AA |          575 |          JFK |               EGE |            N5DRAA |     280 minute |        1747 mi |             -5 minute |            3 minute |      2013-01-01T17:00:00-05:00 |    2013-01-01T19:50:00-07:00 |\n|            UA |         1597 |          EWR |               EGE |            N24702 |     261 minute |        1726 mi |              1 minute |            3 minute |      2013-01-02T09:28:00-05:00 |    2013-01-02T12:20:00-07:00 |\n|            AA |          575 |          JFK |               EGE |            N631AA |     260 minute |        1747 mi |              5 minute |           16 minute |      2013-01-02T17:00:00-05:00 |    2013-01-02T19:50:00-07:00 |","category":"page"},{"location":"#Weather-cleaning-1","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Weather cleaning","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"Import weather data. Get the first row, rename, remove, and transform to add units.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"julia> weathers_file = CSV.File(\"weather.csv\");\n\njulia> const Weather = row_info(weathers_file);\n\njulia> function get_weather(indexed_airports, row)\n            @name @> row |>\n            Weather |>\n            rename(_,\n                airport_code = name\"origin\",\n                dew_point = name\"dewp\",\n                humidity = name\"humid\",\n                precipitation = name\"precip\",\n                temperature = name\"temp\",\n                visibility = name\"visib\",\n                wind_direction = name\"wind_dir\"\n            ) |>\n            transform(_,\n                dew_point = _.dew_point * °F,\n                humidity = _.humidity / 100,\n                precipitation = _.precipitation * inch,\n                pressure = _.pressure * mbar,\n                temperature = _.temperature * °F,\n                visibility = _.visibility * mi,\n                wind_direction = _.wind_direction * °,\n                wind_gust = _.wind_gust * mi / hr,\n                wind_speed = _.wind_speed * mi / hr,\n                date_time = ZonedDateTime(\n                    _.year,\n                    _.month,\n                    _.day,\n                    _.hour,\n                    indexed_airports[_.airport_code].time_zone,\n                    1\n                )\n            ) |>\n            remove(_,\n                name\"year\",\n                name\"month\",\n                name\"day\",\n                name\"hour\"\n            )\n        end;\n\njulia> weathers =\n        @> weathers_file |>\n        over(_, @_ get_weather(indexed_airports, _));\n\njulia> Peek(weathers)\nShowing 4 of 26115 rows\n|     name\"time_hour\" | name\"airport_code\" | name\"dew_point\" |     name\"humidity\" | name\"precipitation\" | name\"pressure\" | name\"temperature\" | name\"visibility\" | name\"wind_direction\" | name\"wind_gust\" |  name\"wind_speed\" |           name\"date_time\" |\n| -------------------:| ------------------:| ---------------:| ------------------:| -------------------:| --------------:| -----------------:| ----------------:| --------------------:| ---------------:| -----------------:| -------------------------:|\n| 2013-01-01 01:00:00 |                EWR |        26.06 °F |             0.5937 |            0.0 inch |    1012.0 mbar |          39.02 °F |          10.0 mi |                 270° |         missing | 10.35702 mi hr^-1 | 2013-01-01T01:00:00-05:00 |\n| 2013-01-01 02:00:00 |                EWR |        26.96 °F | 0.6163000000000001 |            0.0 inch |    1012.3 mbar |          39.02 °F |          10.0 mi |                 250° |         missing |  8.05546 mi hr^-1 | 2013-01-01T02:00:00-05:00 |\n| 2013-01-01 03:00:00 |                EWR |        28.04 °F | 0.6443000000000001 |            0.0 inch |    1012.5 mbar |          39.02 °F |          10.0 mi |                 240° |         missing |  11.5078 mi hr^-1 | 2013-01-01T03:00:00-05:00 |\n| 2013-01-01 04:00:00 |                EWR |        28.04 °F |             0.6221 |            0.0 inch |    1012.2 mbar |          39.92 °F |          10.0 mi |                 250° |         missing | 12.65858 mi hr^-1 | 2013-01-01T04:00:00-05:00 |","category":"page"},{"location":"#Joining-flights-and-weather-1","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Joining flights and weather","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"I know that the weather data is already sorted by airport_code and hour.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"To mix it with flights, order and Group flights By matching variables. Only use data when the departure_delay is present.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"julia> grouped_flights =\n        @name @> flights |>\n        when(_, @_ _.departure_delay !== missing) |>\n        order(_, (name\"origin\", name\"scheduled_departure_time\")) |>\n        Group(By(_, @_ (_.origin, floor(_.scheduled_departure_time, Hour))));\n\n\njulia> key(first(grouped_flights))\n(\"EWR\", ZonedDateTime(2013, 1, 1, 5, tz\"America/New_York\"))","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"Now mix.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"julia> weathers_to_flights = @name @> mix(name\"inner\",\n            By(weathers, @_ (_.airport_code, _.date_time)),\n            By(grouped_flights, key)\n        );\n","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"Look at the first match.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"julia> a_match = first(weathers_to_flights);\n\n\njulia> weather, (flights_key, flights_value) = a_match;\n\n\njulia> weather\n((name\"time_hour\", \"2013-01-01 05:00:00\"), (name\"airport_code\", \"EWR\"), (name\"dew_point\", 28.04 °F), (name\"humidity\", 0.6443000000000001), (name\"precipitation\", 0.0 inch), (name\"pressure\", 1011.9 mbar), (name\"temperature\", 39.02 °F), (name\"visibility\", 10.0 mi), (name\"wind_direction\", 260°), (name\"wind_gust\", missing), (name\"wind_speed\", 12.65858 mi hr^-1), (name\"date_time\", ZonedDateTime(2013, 1, 1, 5, tz\"America/New_York\")))\n\njulia> flights_key\n(\"EWR\", ZonedDateTime(2013, 1, 1, 5, tz\"America/New_York\"))\n\njulia> Peek(flights_value)\n| name\"carrier\" | name\"flight\" | name\"origin\" | name\"destination\" | name\"tail_number\" | name\"air_time\" | name\"distance\" | name\"departure_delay\" | name\"arrival_delay\" | name\"scheduled_departure_time\" | name\"scheduled_arrival_time\" |\n| -------------:| ------------:| ------------:| -----------------:| -----------------:| --------------:| --------------:| ---------------------:| -------------------:| ------------------------------:| ----------------------------:|\n|            UA |         1545 |          EWR |               IAH |            N14228 |     227 minute |        1400 mi |              2 minute |           11 minute |      2013-01-01T05:15:00-05:00 |    2013-01-01T08:19:00-06:00 |\n|            UA |         1696 |          EWR |               ORD |            N39463 |     150 minute |         719 mi |             -4 minute |           12 minute |      2013-01-01T05:58:00-05:00 |    2013-01-01T07:28:00-06:00 |","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"We're interested in visibility and departure_delay.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"julia> visibility = @name weather.visibility\n10.0 mi\n\njulia> @name over(flights_value, @_ (\n            visibility = visibility,\n            departure_delay = _.departure_delay\n        )) |>\n        Peek\n| name\"visibility\" | name\"departure_delay\" |\n| ----------------:| ---------------------:|\n|          10.0 mi |              2 minute |\n|          10.0 mi |             -4 minute |","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"All together.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"julia> function interested_in(a_match)\n            weather, (flights_key, flights_value) = a_match\n            visibility = @name weather.visibility\n            @name over(flights_value, @_ (\n                visibility = visibility,\n                departure_delay = _.departure_delay\n            ))\n        end;\n\njulia> Peek(interested_in(a_match))\n| name\"visibility\" | name\"departure_delay\" |\n| ----------------:| ---------------------:|\n|          10.0 mi |              2 minute |\n|          10.0 mi |             -4 minute |","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"Use Base.Iterators.flatten to unnest data.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"julia> using Base.Iterators: flatten\n\njulia> data =\n        @name @> weathers_to_flights |>\n        over(_, interested_in) |>\n        flatten |>\n        make_columns |>\n        Rows;\n\n\njulia> Peek(data)\nShowing 4 of 326993 rows\n| name\"visibility\" | name\"departure_delay\" |\n| ----------------:| ---------------------:|\n|          10.0 mi |              2 minute |\n|          10.0 mi |             -4 minute |\n|          10.0 mi |             -5 minute |\n|          10.0 mi |             -2 minute |","category":"page"},{"location":"#Visibility-vs.-departure-delay-1","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Visibility vs. departure delay","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"How does visibility affect departure_delay? Group by visibility.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"julia> by_visibility =\n        @> data |>\n        order(_, name\"visibility\") |>\n        Group(By(_, name\"visibility\"));\n\n\njulia> visibility_group = first(by_visibility);\n\n\njulia> key(visibility_group)\n0.0 mi\n\njulia> value(visibility_group) |> Peek\nShowing 4 of 87 rows\n| name\"visibility\" | name\"departure_delay\" |\n| ----------------:| ---------------------:|\n|           0.0 mi |             -5 minute |\n|           0.0 mi |             -1 minute |\n|           0.0 mi |             -8 minute |\n|           0.0 mi |             -7 minute |","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"Calculate the mean departure_delay.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"julia> using Statistics: mean\n\njulia> @> visibility_group |>\n        value |>\n        over(_, name\"departure_delay\") |>\n        mean\n32.252873563218394 minute","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"For each group.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"julia> get_mean_departure_delay(visibility_group) = @name (\n            visibility = key(visibility_group),\n            mean_departure_delay =\n                (@> visibility_group |>\n                    value |>\n                    over(_, name\"departure_delay\") |>\n                    mean),\n            count = length(value(visibility_group))\n        );\n\njulia> @> by_visibility |>\n            over(_, get_mean_departure_delay) |>\n            Peek(_, 20)\nShowing at most 20 rows\n| name\"visibility\" | name\"mean_departure_delay\" | name\"count\" |\n| ----------------:| --------------------------:| -----------:|\n|           0.0 mi |  32.252873563218394 minute |          87 |\n|          0.06 mi |                22.2 minute |          85 |\n|          0.12 mi |   50.69975186104218 minute |         403 |\n|          0.25 mi |  20.481110254433307 minute |        1297 |\n|           0.5 mi |    32.5890826383624 minute |        1319 |\n|          0.75 mi |   30.06759906759907 minute |         429 |\n|           1.0 mi |   32.24348473566642 minute |        1343 |\n|          1.25 mi |  53.187845303867405 minute |         181 |\n|           1.5 mi |   25.90661478599222 minute |        1542 |\n|          1.75 mi |  43.333333333333336 minute |         132 |\n|           2.0 mi |  22.701923076923077 minute |        2912 |\n|           2.5 mi |   21.18074398249453 minute |        2285 |\n|           3.0 mi |    21.2113218731476 minute |        3374 |\n|           4.0 mi |   19.48311444652908 minute |        2132 |\n|           5.0 mi |   21.10387902695595 minute |        4563 |\n|           6.0 mi |  19.807032301480483 minute |        5944 |\n|           7.0 mi |  19.208963745361118 minute |        7006 |\n|           8.0 mi |   19.98660103910309 minute |        7314 |\n|           9.0 mi |  18.762949476558944 minute |       10985 |\n|          10.0 mi |  10.951549367828692 minute |      273660 |","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"This data suggests that low visibility levels lead to larger departure delays, on average.","category":"page"},{"location":"#Reshaping-1","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Reshaping","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"For this section, I will use data from the Global Historical Climatology Network. I got this idea from the tidyr tutorial.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"julia> file = open(\"climate.txt\");\n\njulia> line = readline(file)\n\"ACW00011604194901TMAX  289  X  289  X  283  X  283  X  289  X  289  X  278  X  267  X  272  X  278  X  267  X  278  X  267  X  267  X  278  X  267  X  267  X  272  X  272  X  272  X  278  X  272  X  267  X  267  X  267  X  278  X  272  X  272  X  272  X  272  X  272  X\"\n\njulia> close(file)","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"Parse the first chunk.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"julia> month_variable = @name (\n            year = parse(Int, SubString(line, 12, 15)),\n            month = parse(Int, SubString(line, 16, 17)),\n            variable = Symbol(SubString(line, 18, 21))\n        )\n((name\"year\", 1949), (name\"month\", 1), (name\"variable\", :TMAX))","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"Parse a day. missing is represented by -9999.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"julia> function get_day(line, day)\n            start = 14 + 8 * day\n            value = parse(Int, line[start:start + 4])\n            @name (day = day, value =\n                if value == -9999\n                    missing\n                else\n                    value\n                end\n            )\n        end;\n\njulia> get_day(line, 1)\n((name\"day\", 1), (name\"value\", 289))","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"over each day.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"julia> days = @> over(1:31, @_ (\n            month_variable...,\n            get_day(line, _)...\n        ));\n\njulia> first(days)\n((name\"year\", 1949), (name\"month\", 1), (name\"variable\", :TMAX), (name\"day\", 1), (name\"value\", 289))","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"Use when to remove missing data;","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"julia> days = @name when(days, @_ _.value !== missing);\n\njulia> first(days)\n((name\"year\", 1949), (name\"month\", 1), (name\"variable\", :TMAX), (name\"day\", 1), (name\"value\", 289))","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"Use transform and remove to create a Date. Note that :TMAX has to be defined outside of the @name macro; otherwise, LightQuery will think that it is a Name.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"julia> get_date(day) =\n        @name @> day |>\n        transform(_, date = Date(_.year, _.month, _.day)) |>\n        remove(_, name\"year\", name\"month\", name\"day\");\n\njulia> TMAX = :TMAX;\n\njulia> get_date(first(days)) == @name (\n            variable = TMAX,\n            value = 289,\n            date = Date(\"1949-01-01\")\n        )\ntrue","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"All together.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"julia> function get_month_variable(line)\n            month_variable = @name (\n                year = parse(Int, SubString(line, 12, 15)),\n                month = parse(Int, SubString(line, 16, 17)),\n                variable = Symbol(SubString(line, 18, 21))\n            )\n            @name @> over(1:31, @_ (\n                month_variable...,\n                get_day(line, _)...\n            )) |>\n            when(_, @_ _.value !== missing) |>\n            over(_, get_date)\n        end;\n\njulia> first(get_month_variable(line)) == @name (\n            variable = TMAX,\n            value = 289,\n            date = Date(\"1949-01-01\")\n        )\ntrue","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"over each line. Use flatten to unnest data.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"julia> climate_data =\n        @> eachline(\"climate.txt\") |>\n        over(_, get_month_variable) |>\n        flatten |>\n        make_columns |>\n        Rows;\n\njulia> Peek(climate_data)\nShowing 4 of 1231 rows\n| name\"variable\" | name\"value\" | name\"date\" |\n| --------------:| -----------:| ----------:|\n|          :TMAX |         289 | 1949-01-01 |\n|          :TMAX |         289 | 1949-01-02 |\n|          :TMAX |         283 | 1949-01-03 |\n|          :TMAX |         283 | 1949-01-04 |","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"Sort and group by date.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"julia> by_date =\n        @> climate_data |>\n        order(_, name\"date\") |>\n        Group(By(_, name\"date\"));\n\njulia> day_variables = first(by_date);\n\njulia> key(day_variables)\n1949-01-01\n\njulia> value(day_variables) |> Peek\nShowing 4 of 5 rows\n| name\"variable\" | name\"value\" | name\"date\" |\n| --------------:| -----------:| ----------:|\n|          :TMAX |         289 | 1949-01-01 |\n|          :TMIN |         217 | 1949-01-01 |\n|          :PRCP |           0 | 1949-01-01 |\n|          :SNOW |           0 | 1949-01-01 |","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"over each variable. Use Name to make a Name. This is unavoidably type-unstable.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"julia> spread_variables(day_variables) = @name (\n            date = key(day_variables),\n            over(\n                value(day_variables),\n                @_ (Name(_.variable), _.value)\n            )...\n        );\n\njulia> spread_variables(day_variables) == @name (\n            date = Date(\"1949-01-01\"),\n            TMAX = 289,\n            TMIN = 217,\n            PRCP = 0,\n            SNOW = 0,\n            SNWD = 0\n        )\ntrue","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"over each day.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"julia> @> by_date |>\n        over(_, spread_variables) |>\n        Peek\nShowing at most 4 rows\n| name\"WT16\" | name\"date\" | name\"TMAX\" | name\"TMIN\" | name\"PRCP\" | name\"SNOW\" | name\"SNWD\" |\n| ----------:| ----------:| ----------:| ----------:| ----------:| ----------:| ----------:|\n|    missing | 1949-01-01 |        289 |        217 |          0 |          0 |          0 |\n|          1 | 1949-01-02 |        289 |        228 |         30 |          0 |          0 |\n|    missing | 1949-01-03 |        283 |        222 |          0 |          0 |          0 |\n|          1 | 1949-01-04 |        283 |        233 |          0 |          0 |          0 |","category":"page"},{"location":"#Interface-1","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Interface","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"Modules = [LightQuery]","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"Usage and performance notes","text":"Modules = [LightQuery]","category":"page"},{"location":"#LightQuery.Apply","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"LightQuery.Apply","text":"struct Apply{Names}\n\nApply Names to unnamed values.\n\njulia> using LightQuery\n\njulia> using Test: @inferred\n\njulia> @name @inferred Apply((name\"a\", name\"b\", name\"c\", name\"d\", name\"e\", name\"f\"))((1, 1.0, 1, 1.0, 1, 1.0))\n((name\"a\", 1), (name\"b\", 1.0), (name\"c\", 1), (name\"d\", 1.0), (name\"e\", 1), (name\"f\", 1.0))\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#LightQuery.Backwards","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"LightQuery.Backwards","text":"Backwards(something)\n\nReverse sorting order.\n\njulia> using LightQuery\n\njulia> using Test: @inferred\n\njulia> collect(@inferred order([1, -2], Backwards))\n2-element Array{Int64,1}:\n  1\n -2\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#LightQuery.By","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"LightQuery.By","text":"By(sorted, key_function)\n\nMark that sorted has been pre-sorted by key_function. Use with Group, or mix.\n\njulia> using LightQuery\n\njulia> using Test: @inferred\n\njulia> @inferred By([1, -2], abs)\nBy{Array{Int64,1},typeof(abs)}([1, -2], abs)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#LightQuery.Enumerate","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"LightQuery.Enumerate","text":"Enumerate{Unenumerated}\n\n\"Sees through\" most iterators into their parent.\n\njulia> using LightQuery\n\njulia> using Test: @inferred\n\njulia> @inferred collect(Enumerate(when([4, 3, 2, 1], iseven)))\n2-element Array{Tuple{Int64,Int64},1}:\n (1, 4)\n (3, 2)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#LightQuery.Group-Tuple{By}","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"LightQuery.Group","text":"Group(ungrouped::By)\n\nGroup consecutive keys in ungrouped.\n\njulia> using LightQuery\n\njulia> using Test: @inferred\n\njulia> @inferred collect(Group(By([1, -1, -2, 2, 3, -3], abs)))\n3-element Array{Tuple{Int64,SubArray{Int64,1,Array{Int64,1},Tuple{UnitRange{Int64}},true}},1}:\n (1, [1, -1])\n (2, [-2, 2])\n (3, [3, -3])\n\njulia> (@inferred collect(Group(By(Int[], abs)))) == []\ntrue\n\nRequires a presorted object (see By); order first if not.\n\njulia> using LightQuery\n\njulia> using Test: @inferred\n\njulia> first_group =\n        @> [2, 1, 2, 1] |>\n        order(_, identity) |>\n        Group(By(_, identity)) |>\n        first;\n\njulia> key(first_group)\n1\n\njulia> collect(value(first_group))\n2-element Array{Int64,1}:\n 1\n 1\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#LightQuery.Length","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"LightQuery.Length","text":"Length(iterator, new_length)\n\nAllow optimizations based on length.\n\njulia> using LightQuery\n\njulia> collect(Length(when(1:4, iseven), 2))\n2-element Array{Int64,1}:\n 2\n 4\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#LightQuery.Name-Tuple{Any}","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"LightQuery.Name","text":"Name(name)\n\nCreate a typed Name. Inverse of unname. See also @name_str.\n\njulia> using LightQuery\n\njulia> Name(:a)\nname\"a\"\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#LightQuery.Peek-Tuple{Any}","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"LightQuery.Peek","text":"Peek(rows, maximum_length = 4)\n\nPeek an iterator which returns named tuples. Will show no more than maximum_length rows.\n\njulia> using LightQuery\n\njulia> @name Peek(Rows((a = 1:5, b = 5:-1:1)))\nShowing 4 of 5 rows\n| name\"a\" | name\"b\" |\n| -------:| -------:|\n|       1 |       5 |\n|       2 |       4 |\n|       3 |       3 |\n|       4 |       2 |\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#LightQuery.Rows-Tuple{Any}","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"LightQuery.Rows","text":"Rows(named_columns)\n\nIterator over rows of a table. Always lazy. Use Peek to view.\n\njulia> using LightQuery\n\njulia> using Test: @inferred\n\njulia> lazy = @name @inferred Rows((a = [1, 2], b = [1.0, 2.0]))\n2-element Rows{Tuple{Tuple{Name{:a},Int64},Tuple{Name{:b},Float64}},1,Tuple{Array{Int64,1},Array{Float64,1}},Tuple{Name{:a},Name{:b}}}:\n ((name\"a\", 1), (name\"b\", 1.0))\n ((name\"a\", 2), (name\"b\", 2.0))\n\njulia> @inferred collect(lazy)\n2-element Array{Tuple{Tuple{Name{:a},Int64},Tuple{Name{:b},Float64}},1}:\n ((name\"a\", 1), (name\"b\", 1.0))\n ((name\"a\", 2), (name\"b\", 2.0))\n\njulia> @name @inferred Rows((a = [1, 2],))\n2-element Rows{Tuple{Tuple{Name{:a},Int64}},1,Tuple{Array{Int64,1}},Tuple{Name{:a}}}:\n ((name\"a\", 1),)\n ((name\"a\", 2),)\n\nAll arguments to Rows must have the same axes. Use @inbounds to override the check.\n\njulia> result = @name Rows((a = 1:2, b = 1:3))\nERROR: DimensionMismatch(\"All arguments to `Rows` must have the same axes\")\n[...]\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#LightQuery.gather-Tuple{Any,Vararg{Any,N} where N}","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"LightQuery.gather","text":"gather(data, new_name_old_names...)\n\nFor each new_name, old_names pair in new_name_old_names, gather the old_names into a single new_name. Inverse of spread.\n\njulia> using LightQuery\n\njulia> using Test: @inferred\n\njulia> data = @name (a = 1, b = 1.0, c = 1, d = 1.0, e = 1, f = 1.0);\n\n\njulia> @name @inferred gather(data, g = (name\"b\", name\"e\"), h = (name\"c\", name\"f\"))\n((name\"a\", 1), (name\"d\", 1.0), (name\"g\", ((name\"b\", 1.0), (name\"e\", 1))), (name\"h\", ((name\"c\", 1), (name\"f\", 1.0))))\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#LightQuery.index-Tuple{Any,Any}","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"LightQuery.index","text":"index(unindexed, key_function)\n\nIndex unindexed by the results of key_function. Results of key_function must be unique.\n\njulia> using LightQuery\n\njulia> using Test: @inferred\n\njulia> result = @inferred index([-2, 1], abs)\nLightQuery.Indexed{Int64,Int64,Array{Int64,1},Dict{Int64,Int64}} with 2 entries:\n  2 => -2\n  1 => 1\n\njulia> @inferred result[2]\n-2\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#LightQuery.key-Tuple{Any}","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"LightQuery.key","text":"key(pair)\n\nThe key in a key => value pair.\n\njulia> using LightQuery\n\njulia> using Test: @inferred\n\njulia> @inferred key(:a => 1)\n:a\n\njulia> @inferred key((:a, 1))\n:a\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#LightQuery.make_columns-Tuple{Any}","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"LightQuery.make_columns","text":"make_columns(rows)\n\nCollect into columns.\n\njulia> using LightQuery\n\njulia> using Test: @inferred\n\njulia> stable(x) = @name (a = x, b = x + 0.0, c = x, d = x + 0.0, e = x, f = x + 0.0);\n\njulia> @inferred make_columns(over(1:4, stable))\n((name\"a\", [1, 2, 3, 4]), (name\"b\", [1.0, 2.0, 3.0, 4.0]), (name\"c\", [1, 2, 3, 4]), (name\"d\", [1.0, 2.0, 3.0, 4.0]), (name\"e\", [1, 2, 3, 4]), (name\"f\", [1.0, 2.0, 3.0, 4.0]))\n\njulia> unstable(x) =\n            @name if x <= 2\n                (a = missing, b = string(x), d = string(x))\n            else\n                (a = x, b = missing, c = x)\n            end;\n\njulia> make_columns(over(1:4, unstable))\n((name\"d\", Union{Missing, String}[\"1\", \"2\", missing, missing]), (name\"a\", Union{Missing, Int64}[missing, missing, 3, 4]), (name\"b\", Union{Missing, String}[\"1\", \"2\", missing, missing]), (name\"c\", Union{Missing, Int64}[missing, missing, 3, 4]))\n\njulia> make_columns(when(over(1:4, unstable), row -> true))\n((name\"d\", Union{Missing, String}[\"1\", \"2\", missing, missing]), (name\"a\", Union{Missing, Int64}[missing, missing, 3, 4]), (name\"b\", Union{Missing, String}[\"1\", \"2\", missing, missing]), (name\"c\", Union{Missing, Int64}[missing, missing, 3, 4]))\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#LightQuery.mix-Tuple{Name{:inner},Any,Any}","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"LightQuery.mix","text":"mix(::Name{:inner},  left::By, right::By)\n\nFind all pairs where isequal(left.key_function(left.sorted), right.key_function(right.sorted)). Assumes left and right are both strictly sorted (no repeats). If there are repeats, Group first. See By.\n\njulia> using LightQuery\n\njulia> using Test: @inferred\n\njulia> @name @inferred collect(mix(name\"inner\", By([1, -2, 5, -6], abs), By([-1, 3, -4, 6], abs)))\n2-element Array{Tuple{Int64,Int64},1}:\n (1, -1)\n (-6, 6)\n\njulia> (@name @inferred collect(mix(name\"inner\", By(Int[], abs), By(Int[], abs)))) == []\ntrue\n\njulia> (@name @inferred collect(mix(name\"inner\", By([1], abs), By(Int[], abs)))) == []\ntrue\n\njulia> (@name @inferred collect(mix(name\"inner\", By(Int[], abs), By([1], abs)))) == []\ntrue\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#LightQuery.mix-Tuple{Name{:left},Any,Any}","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"LightQuery.mix","text":"mix(::Name{:left}, left::By, right::By)\n\nFind all pairs where isequal(left.key_function(left.sorted), right.key_function(right.sorted)), using missing when there is no right match. Assumes left and right are both strictly sorted (no repeats). If there are repeats, Group first. See By.\n\njulia> using LightQuery\n\njulia> @name collect(mix(name\"left\", By([1, -2, 5, -6], abs), By([-1, 3, -4, 6], abs)))\n4-element Array{Tuple{Int64,Union{Missing, Int64}},1}:\n (1, -1)\n (-2, missing)\n (5, missing)\n (-6, 6)\n\njulia> (@name collect(mix(name\"left\", By(Int[], abs), By(Int[], abs)))) == []\ntrue\n\njulia> @name collect(mix(name\"left\", By([1], abs), By(Int[], abs)))\n1-element Array{Tuple{Int64,Union{Missing, Int64}},1}:\n (1, missing)\n\njulia> (@name collect(mix(name\"left\", By(Int[], abs), By([1], abs)))) == []\ntrue\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#LightQuery.mix-Tuple{Name{:outer},Any,Any}","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"LightQuery.mix","text":"mix(::Name{:outer}, left::By, right::By)\n\nFind all pairs where isequal(left.key_function(left.sorted), right.key_function(right.sorted)), using missing when there is no left or right match. Assumes left and right are both strictly sorted (no repeats). If there are repeats, Group first. See By.\n\njulia> using LightQuery\n\njulia> @name collect(mix(name\"outer\", By([1, -2, 5, -6], abs), By([-1, 3, -4, 6], abs)))\n6-element Array{Tuple{Union{Missing, Int64},Union{Missing, Int64}},1}:\n (1, -1)\n (-2, missing)\n (missing, 3)\n (missing, -4)\n (5, missing)\n (-6, 6)\n\njulia> (@name collect(mix(name\"outer\", By(Int[], abs), By(Int[], abs)))) == []\ntrue\n\njulia> @name collect(mix(name\"outer\", By([1], abs), By(Int[], abs)))\n1-element Array{Tuple{Union{Missing, Int64},Union{Missing, Int64}},1}:\n (1, missing)\n\njulia> @name collect(mix(name\"outer\", By(Int[], abs), By([1], abs)))\n1-element Array{Tuple{Union{Missing, Int64},Union{Missing, Int64}},1}:\n (missing, 1)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#LightQuery.mix-Tuple{Name{:right},Any,Any}","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"LightQuery.mix","text":"mix(::Name{:right}, left::By, right::By)\n\nFind all pairs where isequal(left.key_function(left.sorted), right.key_function(right.sorted)), using missing when there is no left match. Assumes left and right are both strictly sorted (no repeats). If there are repeats, Group first. See By.\n\njulia> using LightQuery\n\njulia> @name collect(mix(name\"right\", By([1, -2, 5, -6], abs), By([-1, 3, -4, 6], abs)))\n4-element Array{Tuple{Union{Missing, Int64},Int64},1}:\n (1, -1)\n (missing, 3)\n (missing, -4)\n (-6, 6)\n\njulia> (@name collect(mix(name\"right\", By(Int[], abs), By(Int[], abs)))) == []\ntrue\n\njulia> (@name collect(mix(name\"right\", By([1], abs), By(Int[], abs)))) == []\ntrue\n\njulia> @name collect(mix(name\"right\", By(Int[], abs), By([1], abs)))\n1-element Array{Tuple{Union{Missing, Int64},Int64},1}:\n (missing, 1)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#LightQuery.named_tuple-Tuple{Any}","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"LightQuery.named_tuple","text":"named_tuple(data)\n\nConvert data to a named_tuple (see @name).\n\njulia> using LightQuery\n\njulia> using Test: @inferred\n\njulia> @inferred named_tuple((a = 1, b = 1.0, c = 1, d = 1.0, e = 1, f = 1.0))\n((name\"a\", 1), (name\"b\", 1.0), (name\"c\", 1), (name\"d\", 1.0), (name\"e\", 1), (name\"f\", 1.0))\n\nFor stability working with arbitrary structs, propertynames must constant propagate.\n\njulia> struct MyType\n            a::Int\n            b::Float64\n            c::Int\n            d::Float64\n            e::Int\n            f::Float64\n        end\n\njulia> import Base: propertynames\n\njulia> @inline propertynames(::MyType) = (:a, :b, :c, :d, :e, :f);\n\njulia> @inferred named_tuple(MyType(1, 1.0, 1, 1.0, 1, 1.0))\n((name\"a\", 1), (name\"b\", 1.0), (name\"c\", 1), (name\"d\", 1.0), (name\"e\", 1), (name\"f\", 1.0))\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#LightQuery.order-Tuple{Any,Any}","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"LightQuery.order","text":"order(unordered, key_function; keywords...)\n\nGeneralized sort. keywords will be passed to sort!; see the documentation there for options. Use By to mark that an object has been sorted. If the results of key_function are type unstable, consider using hash ∘ key_function instead.\n\njulia> using LightQuery\n\njulia> using Test: @inferred\n\njulia> collect(@inferred order([-2, 1], abs))\n2-element Array{Int64,1}:\n  1\n -2\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#LightQuery.over-Tuple{Any,Any}","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"LightQuery.over","text":"over(iterator, call)\n\nLazy map with the reverse argument order.\n\njulia> using LightQuery\n\njulia> using Test: @inferred\n\njulia> @inferred collect(over([1, -2, -3, 4], abs))\n4-element Array{Int64,1}:\n 1\n 2\n 3\n 4\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#LightQuery.reduce_rows-Tuple{Any,Any,Vararg{Any,N} where N}","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"LightQuery.reduce_rows","text":"function reduce_rows(rows, a_function, columns...)\n\nReduce a function over each of columns in rows.\n\njulia> using LightQuery\n\njulia> using Test: @inferred\n\njulia> @name @inferred reduce_rows(Rows((a = [1, 1], b = [1.0, 1.0])), +, name\"a\", name\"b\")\n((name\"a\", 2), (name\"b\", 2.0))\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#LightQuery.remove-Tuple{Any,Vararg{Any,N} where N}","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"LightQuery.remove","text":"remove(data, old_names...)\n\nRemove old_names from data.\n\njulia> using LightQuery\n\njulia> using Test: @inferred\n\njulia> data = @name (a = 1, b = 1.0, c = 1, d = 1.0, e = 1, f = 1.0);\n\n\njulia> @name @inferred remove(data, name\"c\", name\"f\")\n((name\"a\", 1), (name\"b\", 1.0), (name\"d\", 1.0), (name\"e\", 1))\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#LightQuery.rename-Tuple{Any,Vararg{Any,N} where N}","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"LightQuery.rename","text":"rename(data, new_name_old_names...)\n\nRename data.\n\njulia> using LightQuery\n\njulia> using Test: @inferred\n\njulia> data = @name (a = 1, b = 1.0, c = 1, d = 1.0, e = 1, f = 1.0);\n\n\njulia> @name @inferred rename(data, c2 = name\"c\", f2 = name\"f\")\n((name\"a\", 1), (name\"b\", 1.0), (name\"d\", 1.0), (name\"e\", 1), (name\"c2\", 1), (name\"f2\", 1.0))\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#LightQuery.row_info-Tuple{CSV.File}","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"LightQuery.row_info","text":"row_info(::CSV.File)\n\nGet row info for the CSV file. Can be used as a type stable selector function.\n\njulia> using LightQuery\n\njulia> using Test: @inferred\n\njulia> using CSV: File\n\njulia> test = File(\"test.csv\");\n\njulia> template = row_info(test)\n(LightQuery.InRow{:a,CSV.Column{Int64,Int64}}([1]), LightQuery.InRow{:b,CSV.Column{Float64,Float64}}([1.0]), LightQuery.InRow{:c,CSV.Column{Int64,Int64}}([1]), LightQuery.InRow{:d,CSV.Column{Float64,Float64}}([1.0]), LightQuery.InRow{:e,CSV.Column{Int64,Int64}}([1]), LightQuery.InRow{:f,CSV.Column{Float64,Float64}}([1.0]))\n\njulia> @inferred template(first(test))\n((name\"a\", 1), (name\"b\", 1.0), (name\"c\", 1), (name\"d\", 1.0), (name\"e\", 1), (name\"f\", 1.0))\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#LightQuery.spread-Tuple{Any,Vararg{Any,N} where N}","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"LightQuery.spread","text":"spread(data, some_names...)\n\nUnnest nested named tuples. Inverse of gather.\n\njulia> using LightQuery\n\njulia> using Test: @inferred\n\njulia> gathered = @name (a = 1, d = 1.0, g = (b = 1.0, e = 1), h = (c = 1, f = 1.0));\n\n\njulia> @name @inferred spread(gathered, name\"g\", name\"h\")\n((name\"a\", 1), (name\"d\", 1.0), (name\"b\", 1.0), (name\"e\", 1), (name\"c\", 1), (name\"f\", 1.0))\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#LightQuery.transform-Tuple{Any,Vararg{Any,N} where N}","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"LightQuery.transform","text":"transform(data, assignments...)\n\nMerge assignments into data, overwriting old values.\n\njulia> using LightQuery\n\njulia> using Test: @inferred\n\njulia> data = @name (a = 1, b = 1.0, c = 1, d = 1.0, e = 1, f = 1.0);\n\n\njulia> @name @inferred transform(data, c = 2.0, f = 2, g = 1, h = 1.0)\n((name\"a\", 1), (name\"b\", 1.0), (name\"d\", 1.0), (name\"e\", 1), (name\"c\", 2.0), (name\"f\", 2), (name\"g\", 1), (name\"h\", 1.0))\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#LightQuery.unname-Union{Tuple{Name{name}}, Tuple{name}} where name","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"LightQuery.unname","text":"unname(::Name{name}) where name\n\nInverse of Name.\n\njulia> using LightQuery\n\njulia> using Test: @inferred\n\njulia> @inferred unname(Name(:a))\n:a\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#LightQuery.value-Tuple{Any}","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"LightQuery.value","text":"value(pair)\n\nThe value in a key => value pair.\n\njulia> using LightQuery\n\njulia> using Test: @inferred\n\njulia> @inferred value(:a => 1)\n1\n\njulia> @inferred value((:a, 1))\n1\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#LightQuery.when-Tuple{Any,Any}","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"LightQuery.when","text":"when(iterator, call)\n\nLazy filter with the reverse argument order.\n\njulia> using LightQuery\n\njulia> using Test: @inferred\n\njulia> @inferred collect(when(1:4, iseven))\n2-element Array{Int64,1}:\n 2\n 4\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#LightQuery.@>-Tuple{Any}","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"LightQuery.@>","text":"macro >(body)\n\nIf body is in the form object_ |> call_, call @_ on call, and recur on object.\n\njulia> using LightQuery\n\njulia> @> 0 |> _ - 1 |> abs\n1\n\nYou can nest chains:\n\njulia> @> 1 |> (@> _ + 1 |> _ + 1)\n3\n\nHandles interpolations seamlessly:\n\njulia> @> 1 |> :(_ + $_)\n:(_ + 1)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"macro"},{"location":"#LightQuery.@_-Tuple{Any}","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"LightQuery.@_","text":"macro _(body)\n\nTerser function syntax. The arguments are inside the body; the first argument is _, the second argument is __, etc. Will @inline.\n\njulia> using LightQuery\n\njulia> using Test: @inferred\n\njulia> @inferred (@_ _ + 1)(1)\n2\n\njulia> @inferred map((@_ __ - _), (1, 2), (2, 1))\n(1, -1)\n\nIf there are no _ arguments, read as is.\n\njulia> (@_ x -> x + 1)(1)\n2\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"macro"},{"location":"#LightQuery.@if_known-Tuple{Any}","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"LightQuery.@if_known","text":"@if_known(something)\n\nIf something is missing, return missing, otherwise, something.\n\njulia> using LightQuery\n\njulia> using Test: @inferred\n\njulia> function test(x)\n            first(@if_known(x))\n        end;\n\njulia> @inferred test((1, 2))\n1\n\njulia> @inferred test(missing)\nmissing\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"macro"},{"location":"#LightQuery.@name-Tuple{Any}","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"LightQuery.@name","text":"macro name(code)\n\nSwitch to named_tuples.\n\njulia> using LightQuery\n\njulia> using Test: @inferred\n\njulia> data = @name (a = 1, b = 1.0, c = 1, d = 1.0, e = 1, f = 1.0)\n((name\"a\", 1), (name\"b\", 1.0), (name\"c\", 1), (name\"d\", 1.0), (name\"e\", 1), (name\"f\", 1.0))\n\nbased on typed Names.\n\njulia> name\"a\"\nname\"a\"\n\nNames can be used as properties\n\njulia> @name @inferred data.c\n1\n\njulia> @name data.g\nERROR: BoundsError: attempt to access ((name\"a\", 1), (name\"b\", 1.0), (name\"c\", 1), (name\"d\", 1.0), (name\"e\", 1), (name\"f\", 1.0))\n  at index [name\"g\"]\n[...]\n\nand selector functions.\n\njulia> @name @inferred name\"c\"(data)\n1\n\nMultiple names can be used as selector functions\n\njulia> @name @inferred (name\"c\", name\"f\")(data)\n((name\"c\", 1), (name\"f\", 1.0))\n\nYou can also convert back to NamedTuples.\n\njulia> @inferred NamedTuple(data)\n(a = 1, b = 1.0, c = 1, d = 1.0, e = 1, f = 1.0)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"macro"},{"location":"#LightQuery.@name_str-Tuple{Any}","page":"Usage and performance notes","title":"LightQuery.@name_str","text":"name_str(name)\n\nCreate a typed Name.\n\njulia> using LightQuery\n\njulia> name\"a\"\nname\"a\"\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"macro"}]
